      "fields": [
        "What is cosine similarity?",
        "<b>Intuition:</b> Measure angle between vectors (direction, not magnitude)<br>\n<b>Formula:</b> cos(θ) = A·B / (||A|| × ||B||)<br>\n<b>Range:</b> [-1,1] where 1=same direction, 0=orthogonal<br>\n<b>Use:</b> Document similarity, recommendation systems",
        "Similarity & Distance Metrics",
        "concept"
      ],
      "guid": "nlp_f745833893aaa",
      "note_model_uuid": "nlp-similarity_metrics-model",
      "tags": [
        "similarity__distance_metrics",
        "concept"
      ]
    },
    {
      "__type__": "Note",
      "fields": [
        "Cosine vs Euclidean similarity?",
        "<b>Cosine:</b> Measures direction (angle) - length independent<br>\n<b>Euclidean:</b> Measures distance - sensitive to magnitude<br>\n<b>Text:</b> Cosine better (document length varies)<br>\n<b>Images:</b> Euclidean often used (pixel intensities matter)",
        "Similarity & Distance Metrics",
        "concept"
      ],
      "guid": "nlp_9438a4be44c24",
      "note_model_uuid": "nlp-similarity_metrics-model",
      "tags": [
        "similarity__distance_metrics",
        "concept"
      ]
    },
    {
      "__type__": "Note",
      "fields": [
        "What is Jaccard similarity?",
        "<b>Formula:</b> |A ∩ B| / |A ∪ B|<br>\n<b>Interpretation:</b> Overlap divided by union<br>\n<b>Range:</b> [0,1] where 1=identical sets<br>\n<b>Use:</b> Set similarity, document deduplication",
        "Similarity & Distance Metrics",
        "concept"
      ],
      "guid": "nlp_38490434aa8b4",
      "note_model_uuid": "nlp-similarity_metrics-model",
      "tags": [
        "similarity__distance_metrics",
        "concept"
      ]
    },
    {
      "__type__": "Note",
      "fields": [
        "What is edit distance (Levenshtein)?",
        "<b>Definition:</b> Minimum edits to transform one string to another<br>\n<b>Operations:</b> Insert, delete, substitute<br>\n<b>Algorithm:</b> Dynamic programming O(mn)<br>\n<b>Applications:</b> Spell correction, fuzzy matching",
        "Similarity & Distance Metrics",
        "concept"
